    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Windows Azure - Connect to Linux Virtual Machine]]></title>
    <link href="http://www.deepakkapoor.net/2013/05/31/windows-azure-connect-to-linux-virtual-machine/"/>
    <updated>2013-05-31T00:00:00+10:00</updated>
    <id>http://www.deepakkapoor.net/2013/05/31/windows-azure-connect-to-linux-virtual-machine</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In an <a href="http://www.debugrelease.com/2013/05/30/windows-azure-create-linux-virtual-machine-through-management-portal/">earlier post</a> I created a Linux virtual machine on Windows Azure. In this post I will show you how to establish a SSH connection to the virtual machine.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>Windows</h4>


<p>Windows does not come with a SSH client but we can use <a href="http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/download.html">PuTTY</a> to make SSH connections from a Windows machine.</p>

<p>Open putty.exe and enter host information as it is on the management portal.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/SNAGHTML3b92ce5e.png"><img style="background-image: none; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px; border-width: 0px;" title="SNAGHTML3b92ce5e" alt="SNAGHTML3b92ce5e" src="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/SNAGHTML3b92ce5e_thumb.png" width="470" height="453" border="0" /></a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Click Open and you are asked to login. Enter username and password and you are logged into the Linux virtual machine.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/SNAGHTML3b9558d2.png"><img style="background-image: none; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px; border-width: 0px;" title="SNAGHTML3b9558d2" alt="SNAGHTML3b9558d2" src="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/SNAGHTML3b9558d2_thumb.png" width="644" height="406" border="0" /></a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>Linux Terminal</h4>


<p>Logging into Linux virtual machine on Windows Azure from a Linux terminal is dead simple. Linux already comes with a OpenSSH client so there is nothing to be installed.</p>

<p>Just run the ssh command with correct port number and host. In my case the command is</p>

<p class="text-info"><span>ssh –p 58473 azureuser@debrelubuntu.cloudapp.net</span></p>


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Enter the correct password when prompted and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob%27s_your_uncle">Bob’s your uncle</a>.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/image10.png"><img style="background-image: none; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px; border-width: 0px;" title="image" alt="image" src="https://googledrive.com/host/0B6PDO8HPEQZNZWpTRms0ZWtlaUU/uploads/2013/05/image_thumb6.png" width="644" height="402" border="0" /></a></p>
]]></content>
